The paper deals with graph-based methods for inference, which is a common topic in machine learning and data science. The use of kernel-based methods and the development of a kernel Kalman filter suggest a focus on learning and estimation, which is often associated with the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with spatiotemporal dynamics and time-evolving topologies, which suggests a focus on network science and complex systems, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely sub-categories as well. The use of numerical tests with real data sets suggests a focus on empirical evaluation, which is often associated with the sub-categories of cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
